    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CANADA PILOTS REJECT ARBITRATION</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Showdown between Air Canada and its 2,200 pilots intensifies as pilots reject management's request to submit contract issues over flight fatigue and pensions to binding arbitration (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A showdown between Air Canada and its 2,200 pilots intensified as the pilots rejected management's request to submit contract issues over flight fatigue and pensions to binding arbitration. The Air Canada Pilots Association has yet to set a strike date, but the possibility remains that the pilots could shut down the airline by the end of the week.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
      </block>
